The following companies had unusual
price changes in Peru trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close of trade in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  was little changed at 19,943.99. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed 0.3 percent to 2,578.97.  Mining stocks gained after gold, silver and tin advanced in
 New York  and  London .  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the worldâ€™s fourth-largest tin
producer, rose 1.9 percent to 2.75 soles.  Cia. Minera Milpo (MILPOC1) 
(MILPOC1 PE), a zinc and silver producer controlled by Sao
Paulo-based Votorantim Metais Ltda., climbed 1.5 percent to 4.77
soles.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner,
gained for a fourth session, adding 1.2 percent to $3.45 after
announcing it increased gold resources by 40 percent at its La
Arena mine.  Copper and zinc miners dropped after the metals declined.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, fell 10 percent to 9 cents.  Rio Cristal
Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian exploration company,
dropped 10 percent to 9 cents.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a
Canadian exploration company, declined 3.1 percent to 93 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
